          @SteveHyland I think 4-3-3 system with Son left, Eriksen right, Kane striker is an option. Alli being the central midfielder with license to get forward. And one anchor man, I'd play Dembele as the other central midfielder and Winks as the sitting mid. I prefer Winks to Dier in a more open game as he has more agility and shifts the ball quickly (even if he hasn't got great passing range and often passes sideways I don't mind it. As it means ball retention and getting it to the attackers quickly. He also has defensive discipline. The obvious positives of Dier are height and power, but I don't think it's needed or the point of opening to a more expansive system). I do think Pochettino is concerned about control and defensive structure first and foremost which is why Spurs struggle and are laboured at times against the weaker sides.
